Posts: 80<br> <font color=#000000>(9/30/03 1:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=358.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A Question from the back of the room!!! please...</span><hr size=1> I've never had an infil, screwed around with my brothers, he's an uber infil but theres also some talent involved. Getting used to your own class I suppose. I mention the infil because we share, or in their case abuse, the DW line.<br>
<br>
What puzzles me is that we all know your Base melee skill, Slash/ Crush/ Thrust dictates your minimum damage done. Your &quot;Advanced&quot; skill (mercs dont have) dictates your chance to do maximum damage.<br>
<br>
Presumably in this case DW is the infils base skill and CS his advanced. As DW is his base (auto nerf mercs maybe) then why, and I've seen this alot wit infils taking purps in DF, do infils raise their base DW to nothing and still do massive damage almost all the time?<br>
<br>
My Bro's infil has CS at 50 and DW at....wait for it.....10! thats right 10, and it seems to make almost no difference to his abilities. Many infils have now told me this. They ridicule DW at best (who can blame em) His argument was that he needed the points for Stealth and Envenom of course but...sheeesh...<br>
<br>
I know many Merc's here have done constant tests. Many other pallies, Arms too. It is always argued that there must be a minimum base otherwise diminishing returns, unstyled you'd suck, often even styled you could suck.<br>
<br>
Are infils a special case? I thought there were no special cases?<br>
<br>
This is and has got to ba a basic math excersise after all.<br>
<br>
My base is 39 with items making it 51. Due to Mythics earlier comments about going above 50 getting real minimal returns I didn't take it much higher. I'd be frightened to go much lower.<br>
<br>
Why is this? Are we all making a mistake and need to learn the infils secret? Have they just exposed a flaw?<br>
<br>
Regards, <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kerrecsnowmane>Kerrec Snowmane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mercenary TL</span><br>  Posts: 139<br> <font color=#000000>(9/30/03 2:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=358.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Question from the back of the room!!! please...</span><hr size=1> Your Dual Wield spec has nothing to do with your damage variance (per hit).<br>
<br>
The only thing that affects your damage variance, is your base weapon spec.  Same goes for Infiltrators.  I imagine your brothers infiltrator has a decent spec in his base weapon.<br>
<br>
ALL spec'ing in Dual Wield does, is open up new styles, and increase your CHANCE to double attack in any given round of combat.  <p>Kerrec Snowmane<br>
Mercenary Team Lead<br>
R6L2, Palomides.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grayswandir@lighttanksofdaoc>Grayswandir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#000000>(9/30/03 3:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=358.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Question from the back of the room!!! please...</span><hr size=1> Yes Kerrec, of course, no argument from me.<br>
<br>
I suppose, when re-reading it, I didn't explain as well as I might have. FYI his base is 25.<br>
<br>
What I don't know, and you and others have a better grasp on the math than i do, is how he is dual weilding and keeping his damage up with such low DW and base trains?<br>
<br>
I was just curious.<br>
<br>
Regards, <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nirala>Nirala</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mercenary Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 692<br> <font color=#000000>(9/30/03 5:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=358.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Question from the back of the room!!! please...</span><hr size=1> Aside from opening new styles, and raising DW chance, it also increases your style damage when using DW styles.  (also raises Flurry damage, but that's not really the point of this thread).<br>
<br>
I also disagree, I feel that DW IS in fact an Advanced Spec. <p>Nirala Kindred<br>
&lt;The Kindred&gt;<br>
Gawaine<br>
50 Saracen Slash Merc<br>
Kriege<br>
45 Tri-Spec Cleric</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vasagh>Vasagh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 81<br> <font color=#000000>(10/1/03 12:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=358.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Question from the back of the room!!! please...</span><hr size=1> Dual wield doesn't add much dmg from dual swinging and is the least beneficial spec line when you consider everything else an inf has access to spec in. <br>
<br>
Without putting any points in it a merc/inf/ranger/bm gets 37.5% chance to double swing. Now add in +11 from items and a spec of 25 in it. And that inf is now swinging a bit over 50%. Having 50 base dw will only add another 12.5% but cost a huge amount of spec points better spent elsewhere.<br>
<br>
That 12.5% extra chance to swing translates to even less damage, because the offhand doesn't benefit from styles and misses more, making a very small amount of the total damage in actual fights. <br>
<br>
Now consider that most of the dw styles are pretty mediocre/poor and can easily be replaced by  CS/weapon spec lines. The only dw style that I use regularly myself is the L50 style dual shadows as a merc, that and flurry for mercs only give something extra and because as a merc there isn't much else to spec in it makes it worthwhile to goto 50 but hardly for an inf.<br>
<br>
(There are a few other styles in dw spec like the stun chain which is useful in specific conditions to a merc but one can do without but totally useless to infs who can't parry and have better stuns (dragonfang and perf. chain) available to them).<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xainder>Xainder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 121<br> <font color=#000000>(10/1/03 10:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=358.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Question from the back of the room!!! please...</span><hr size=1> Nirala:<br>
DW spec &quot;... also increases your style damage when using DW styles.&quot;<br>
<br>
I challange you to prove this. I would really like it to be the case, but i've seen nothing in my own testing, or in other peoples tests, that shows this to be true. I would really love to be proven wrong though, since i'm spec'ed 50 in DW. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nirala>Nirala</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mercenary Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 695<br> <font color=#000000>(10/1/03 11:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=358.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Question from the back of the room!!! please...</span><hr size=1> Okay.  The Growth Rate (for simplicity's sake, the style multiplier) is based on your spec in the line of the style you use, DW in this case.  This is then multiplied by the base damage (generated by your Base weapon spec of whatever type you're styling with).  Now, the easiest way to verify this would be to respec on Pendragon.  With 50 Base weapon spec, test one of the low lvl styles (not the starter style) on one of the grays outside Cammy with super low DW, then spec it all the way up, and see what your new cap is. <p>Nirala Kindred<br>
&lt;The Kindred&gt;<br>
Gawaine<br>
50 Saracen Slash Merc<br>
Kriege<br>
45 Tri-Spec Cleric</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grayswandir@lighttanksofdaoc>Grayswandir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#000000>(10/1/03 11:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=358.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The question...</span><hr size=1> Vasagh,<br>
Thanks, for the clear concise explanation. you have, I think answered my question. I think you nailed it, as I said I' not experienced with an infil although I know many here have them. The sharing of our DW line always makes us curious about others that use it and their benefits from it - if any. Thanks.<br>
<br>
Xainder,<br>
I agree with your point. In my own tests there is no DW style (DS the jury is still out on that one due to a re-spec) that increases my damage signifigantly over my base style in general. It is not only that DW styles are poor, but we must continue to use our base styles for results in many situations.<br>
<br>
My argument remains the same; Many classes receive an advanced weapon spec with unique abilities and or damage etc. They never go back to their base styles nor have to.<br>
<br>
The Mercenary receives, no matter how you wish to define it, the equivalent of two &quot;base&quot; weapon styles. And, remember, the Merc also receives the same penalties of having to spec two weapon styles that all other AWS characters have without the benefits.<br>
<br>
The only &quot;defense&quot; I am given is that it gives the Merc more &quot;chance&quot; to swing the off-hand. This, as some try to argue DW is AWS, is an awfully poor substitute.<br>
<br>
Regards, <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vasagh>Vasagh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#000000>(10/1/03 12:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=358.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The question...</span><hr size=1> Nirala:<br>
DW spec &quot;... also increases your style damage when using DW styles.&quot;<br>
<br>
He is absolutely correct. The unstyled damage isn't based on DW but your style bonus when using DW styles is based on your spec in DW. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xainder>Xainder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 122<br> <font color=#000000>(10/1/03 3:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=358.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The question...</span><hr size=1> I stand corrected. DW Spec does in fact directly effect the 'damage bonus' and the 'damage cap' of a given DW style. my tests were very quick, and with an old copy of Xainder, but the results are obvious.<br>
<br>
DW: 44+5 (6 Attacks)<br>
Flank: Damage Cap = 233, Average Bonus Damage = 537<br>
<br>
DW: 50+5 (6 attacks)<br>
Flank: Damage Cap = 241, Average Bonus Damage = 573<br>
<br>
As i said, these were <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>very</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> quick tests, but conclusive enough for me to show that a higher DW spec does in fact give you higher damage and damage caps when doing DW styles. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nirala>Nirala</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mercenary Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 696<br> <font color=#000000>(10/1/03 4:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=358.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The question...</span><hr size=1> Grayswandir, I'm curious what styles you use.  As a slash merc the only 2 slash styles on my Qbar are Amy Slash (for when it's just TOO chaotic to get a positional off) and Backslash.  As a crush merc the only crush style I had up was Concussion (well, except for Back Crush off my main qbar page in case I ever wanted to use it).  In my experience I've found DW styles to be FAR superior to all but a couple styles in each base list. <p>Nirala Kindred<br>
