 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rosimond@lighttanksofdaoc>Rosimond</A> at: 10/3/03 4:55 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=blame@lighttanksofdaoc>Blame</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://homepages.internet.lu/lordoftherings/images/boromir.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Old-Timer</span><br>  Posts: 515<br> <font color=#000000>(10/4/03 3:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=358.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> styles</span><hr size=1> For an infiltrator, Thrust (or slash! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) is your <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>base</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> weapon spec. This will determine your standard unstyled or offhand damage, modified by your offensive stats.<br>
<br>
The same goes for a merc. Let's clarify this <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
The style bonus which is applied to mainhand is affected by your spec in the 'advanced' weapon spec. Basically, the advanced spec is the spec with styles you can do with more than one type of weapon (eg pole arms, DW --as long as you have 2 weapons--, 2Handed and Critical Strike moves.<br>
<br>
Speccing and +ing to CS or DW will mean when you do a CS or a DW style you have a higher damage cap. I am slightly curious how this works, seeing as style modifiers are supposed to be fixed (is flank really 85% is you don't have any DW spec??), but. Honestly, I'm <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>way</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> through caring. My non-SC'd merc chews up orange slash-resistant mobs with no offensive RAs at all.<br>
<br>
OK. The DW styles are sucky. Nothing much has changed, maybe a few dodgy% here and there, but DS and DT have their benefits (probably 1 or 2 fumbles from an OJ mob means you are spared about 120 damage?). What the DW styles do have going for them is utility.<br>
<br>
Not perfect utility, because we have evade1 and nothing amazing coming off that compared to our parry-stun, but at least we have a parry stun which I use on Needletooth devourers in Barfog, and also that Skald who I got twice in Doden's gruva. Haha.  But we have a Bleed that we can refresh whenever we like (even if it don't interrupt casters at all) and if we attack a Neutral mob, we can nerf their attacking speed (which helps us a lot) before the fight has even begun. <br>
<br>
Our Anytime sucks, but don't use it. Use Slash-Crush-Thrust anytime, or get in position (you're probably already in it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) and use DS. Ration your Endurance if you're in a long drawn- out fight and do DS every 3 or 4 hits. Who said only Paladins get Gain over Time?<br>
<br>
DW styles offer a lot of choice and utility for PvE, a bit harder to make the most of them for RvR. We could still use something to make Tendrils worth using, a back-based equivalent of Flank-Rain (or of Flank-Dark for RvR, seeing as we have 3 styles in this weird triangle and they have been forsaken somewhat) and an anytime that people don't laugh at, but we're not missing out on all that much. At least, not unless you're like me and you want Body bleeds to stack with Cold bleeds.<br>
<br>
-Blame, EXCAL<br>
<br>
I used to hate DW styles, then I realised they were actually sort of acceptable.<br>
<br>
