<br>
The growth rate is not the multiplier and cannot be used as a percentage. You put the growth rate in the formula and you get the multiplier. It's the multiplier that changes based on your spec and swing speed. Which then you multiply to the base dmg to get the style bonus. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vasagh>Vasagh</A> at: 10/5/03 12:35 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=blame@lighttanksofdaoc>Blame</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://homepages.internet.lu/lordoftherings/images/boromir.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Old-Timer</span><br>  Posts: 523<br> <font color=#000000>(10/5/03 3:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=358.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> clarification</span><hr size=1> I'm a bit confused here, and we're off on a tangent but...<br>
